topic_title:
AWS Data Pipeline
      Data Pipeline Object Fields

variables.description: Specifies the name of a field for a particular object. To view fields for a                   data pipeline object, see Pipeline Object Reference in the                      AWS Data Pipeline Developer Guide.
variables.name: Key

variables.description: A field value that you specify as an identifier of another object in the same                   pipeline definition.
variables.name: RefValue
variables.required: Conditional if the key that you are using requires it.

variables.description: A field value that you specify as a string. To view valid values for a                   particular field, see Pipeline                      Object Reference in the AWS Data Pipeline Developer Guide.
variables.name: StringValue
variables.required: Conditional if the key that you are using requires it.
